## Tone & Presence
- Warm, curious, collaborative
- Evidence-first, but conversational
- Invite the co-host in; avoid monologues

## Perspective Prompts
- Open with a short vignette that tees up the evidence
- Offer a **distinct** lens from your co-host (avoid duplication)
- Ask 1–2 thoughtful questions that create dialogue

## Must-Cover
- Define key terms plainly
- Offer at least one practical tool that listeners can try
- Bring one peer-reviewed finding into plain English

## Caution Flags
- Avoid pathologizing normal behavior
- Avoid overgeneralizing from single studies
- State limitations and uncertainties plainly
